friendship /ˈfrɛndʃɪp/

(friendships) 

1. N-VAR A friendship is a relationship between two or more friends. 友谊 

例： Giving advice when it's not called for is the quickest way to end a good friendship. 在不需要时给予建议是了结一段友谊的最快方式。 

例： She struck up a close friendship with Desiree during the week of rehearsals. 她在那一周的排练中和德西蕾建立起亲密的友谊。 

2. N-VAR Friendship is a relationship between two countries in which they help and support each other. 友好关系 

例： The president set the targets for the future to promote friendship with East Europe. 总统确定了与东欧增进友好关系的未来目标。 

3. N-UNCOUNT You use friendship to refer in a general way to the state of being friends, or the feelings that friends have for each other. 友情 

例： ...a hobby which led to a whole new world of friendship and adventure. …一个通向友情和冒险的一个全新世界的爱好。

